  "texts": [
    "The Centrality-GAT model incorporates higher-order topological features in addition to the GAT model.",
    "On the other hand, the EdgeAdj-Transformer-GAT model and the TWC-GNN model differ in terms of the edge matrix weights, which are restricted to binary values of 0 and 1.",
    "The empirical findings suggest that higher-order topological structures have superior capability in capturing intricate relationships inside the network, hence leading to enhanced accuracy of the model.",
    "In this paper, we have presented the TWC-GNN model, designed for the node classification task within directed graphs by leveraging higher-order topological structures and self-attention mechanisms.",
